    "abstractNote": "This article contributes to the study of Christian Arabic literature by providing an introduction and English translation of the treatise entitled <i>Kayfiyyat idr\u0101k \u1e25aq\u012bqat al-diy\u0101na</i>, \u2018On how to discern the truth of religion\u2019, by the prominent Baghdad-based Nestorian physician, scholar and translator, \u1e24unayn b. Is\u1e25\u0101q (808-873). This work constitutes a defence of Christianity in a multi-religious milieu marked by the ascendency of Islam. \u1e24unayn discusses therein the reasons that lead people to adhere to a particular religion, his main contention being that the truth or falsity of any religion can be ascertained by examining the reasons why it was originally accepted.",
